        <div class="col-md-8 font-weight-bold" id="instructions">
            <h5>Instructions</h5>
            <ol>
                <li>Preheat oven to 400 degrees.</li>
                <li>In a small baking dish combine tomatoes, garlic, oregano, and olive oil along with a pinch of salt.
                    Toss to coat the tomatoes evenly.</li>
                <li>Roast for 30 minutes.
                </li>
                <li>While the tomatoes are roasting, add balsamic vinegar to a small saucepan over medium-high heat.
                </li>
                <li>Bring to a simmer, reduce heat and gently simmer for 12-15 minutes, or until it reduces by about
                    half and it easily coats the back of a spoon. Set aside to cool.
                </li>
                <li>Remove roasted tomatoes from the oven and top with burrata. Drizzle with balsamic reduction and
                    garnish with fresh basil.
                </li>
                <li>Serve with sliced French baguette and enjoy!
                </li>
            </ol>
        </div>
        <div class="col-md-2" id="ingredients">
            <h5>Ingredients</h5>
            <ul>
                <li>2 pints grape tomatoes</li>
                <li>4 cloves garlic, thinly sliced</li>
                <li>2-3 tablespoons olive oil</li>
                <li>1/2 teaspoon dried oregano</li>
                <li>kosher salt</li>
                <li>8 oz. burrata cheese</li>
                <li>1/2 cup balsamic vinegar</li>
                <li>fresh basil for garnish</li>
                <li>sliced French baguette for serving</li>
            </ul>
        </div>
    </div>
